President Obama has declared a major disaster in Massachusetts due to a severe winter storm and snowstorm that occurred in January 2011. Federal aid will be provided to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available for emergency work, including snow assistance, as well as for hazard mitigation measures. James N. Russo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA.